Two men, believed to be towing operators, were killed after a truck crashed into them while they were assessing another truck that had broken down on the N2, in the vicinity of the Umhlanga Rocks area on Sunday night. Shawn Herbst, Netcare 911 spokesperson, said a truck crashed into the back of another broken down truck where two towing operators were busy assessing the broken-down truck. The incident happened just after 10 pm. Herbst said the two men died on the scene. Herbst said the circumstances leading up to the incident will be investigated by the relevant authorities.